title: H.S. football: Don Bosco takes on No. 1 team tonight
text:
H.S. football: Don Bosco takes on No. 1 team tonight October 23, 2015 Last updated: Friday, October 23, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record Print 
In a season filled with some remarkable out-of-state challenges, Don Bosco obviously saved the best and biggest for last. 
The Ironmen (4-2), ranked No. 4 in The Record non-public football Top 6, will travel to Las Vegas tonight to take on Bishop Gorman (8-0), the No. 1 team in most national high school polls. 
The Gaels already have beaten five notable national programs this season, outscoring the opposition, 400-82. 
Bosco, ranked as high as No. 26 in the nation, has lost two games by a combined 13 points, including a final-seconds loss to Paramus Catholic two weeks ago. 
The Ironmen may be the biggest team up front that the Gaels have faced this season, and they have a history of rising to the occasion in these sort of games. 
Most of the 82 points Bishop Gorman has allowed have come against its second-team defense. But Don Bosco has been able to consistently run the ball, led by senior running back Malik Bakker. 
— Mark J. Czerwinski © 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
